    <fr:title text="Internal categories as models of a theory">Internal categories as models of a theory</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The notion of a (meta-)category is an essentially algebraic theory. As such it is possible to compute <fr:em>models</fr:em> of this theory in any category that has finite limits.</fr:p>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors />
        <fr:addr>frct-001A</fr:addr>
        <fr:route>frct-001A.xml</fr:route>
        <fr:title text="Internal category">Internal category</fr:title>
        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> be a category with finite limits; then an <fr:em>internal category</fr:em>
in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is defined by the following data:</fr:p>
        <fr:ol><fr:li>an object of objects <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{0}\in  E]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li>an object of morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{1}\in  E]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li>source and target morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s,t:C_{1}\to  C_{0}]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li>a generic identity morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{0}\to  C_{1}]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li>a generic composition morphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{1}\times _{C_{0}}C_{1}\to  C_{1}]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li>satisfying a number of laws corresponding to those of a category.</fr:li></fr:ol>
        <fr:p>For the details of these laws, we refer to any standard source.</fr:p>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
  </fr:mainmatter>
